According to the analysis of Nesbitt and his colleagues, Tawa hallae is a primitive theropode.
This shows an interesting combination of primitive and progressive properties, comments Nesbitt.
For example, in Tawa’s skull, researchers found signs of air bags, such as those that also possess the descendants of theropods, birds.
Thanks to air bags, the breathing of birds is more efficient than that of mammals.
In the case of Tawa findae also the bones of the spine were obviously filled with air partially.
Tawa is the oldest and primitive airbag theropode, comments Randall Irmis.
Because the relative line of later giant sauropods also possessed air bags and light bones, it was likely that the common predecessors of both groups would already produce this useful innovation.
At least three migratory waves to North America
Because the most primitive dinosaurs so far known lived in South America, researchers deduce that the sauries emerged there for the first time.
Consequently, the three genealogic lineages were separated in the beginning and spread from South America to all the corners of Earth, which at the time still formed a unique earthly mass, the Pangea supercontinent.
However, the facts say the team found together with Tawa finds the remains of two other theropods not very intimately related.
