While in the Triasic, dinosaurs still shared their life space with many other reptiles, for example with the ancestors of the current crocodiles and the pterosaurians and many other sauries.
Towards the end of the Triasic, the dinosaurs expanded throughout the world and developed many new species, while relativeness extinct at the border of the Triasic towards the Jurassic.
Successful stories were not eternal
